00:13:33.280 --> 00:13:35.350 align:middle line:84%
Schumann waves have
been part of this planet

00:13:35.350 --> 00:13:38.150 align:middle line:90%
since the very beginning.

00:13:38.150 --> 00:13:45.550 align:middle line:84%
Life evolves surrounded by
them and inevitably tuned in.

00:13:45.550 --> 00:13:49.010 align:middle line:84%
In fact, our
sensitivity to frequency

00:13:49.010 --> 00:13:52.130 align:middle line:84%
became deeply connected to
our ability to sense another

00:13:52.130 --> 00:13:53.180 align:middle line:90%
of the planet's phenomena.

00:13:53.180 --> 00:14:05.648 align:middle line:90%


00:14:05.648 --> 00:14:09.850 align:middle line:84%
Two billion years ago
magnetotatic bacteria

00:14:09.850 --> 00:14:12.810 align:middle line:84%
formed a simple but intriguing
relationship with the Earth's

00:14:12.810 --> 00:14:15.260 align:middle line:90%
magnetic fields.

00:14:15.260 --> 00:14:17.170 align:middle line:84%
The single-celled
organism contained

00:14:17.170 --> 00:14:20.000 align:middle line:90%
particles of magnetic material.

00:14:20.000 --> 00:14:22.770 align:middle line:84%
This enabled it to act like
the needle of a compass

00:14:22.770 --> 00:14:25.306 align:middle line:84%
and orient along the
magnetic lines of the Earth.

00:14:25.306 --> 00:14:28.390 align:middle line:90%


00:14:28.390 --> 00:14:31.110 align:middle line:84%
As organisms became
more complex,

00:14:31.110 --> 00:14:33.370 align:middle line:84%
so did their reliance on
the Earth's magnetic fields.

00:14:33.370 --> 00:14:53.620 align:middle line:90%


00:14:53.620 --> 00:14:56.160 align:middle line:84%
We do know that bees are
sensitive to magnetic fields.

00:14:56.160 --> 00:14:57.640 align:middle line:84%
We know that within
their bodies they

00:14:57.640 --> 00:15:01.120 align:middle line:84%
contain particles of Earth
magnetite and laboratory

00:15:01.120 --> 00:15:03.130 align:middle line:84%
studies have shown
that they are indeed

00:15:03.130 --> 00:15:04.740 align:middle line:90%
sensitive to magnetic fields.

00:15:04.740 --> 00:15:08.220 align:middle line:10%
And you can demonstrate
in laboratory

00:15:08.220 --> 00:15:10.860 align:middle line:10%
that if you artificially
create a magnetic field,

00:15:10.860 --> 00:15:14.770 align:middle line:10%
you can control the way
that they build their cone

00:15:14.770 --> 00:15:18.110 align:middle line:10%
and it seems logical
that bees are using

00:15:18.110 --> 00:15:21.110 align:middle line:10%
magnetic fields in navigation.

00:15:21.110 --> 00:15:23.680 align:middle line:84%
NARRATOR: - The delicate
balance of life on Earth

00:15:23.680 --> 00:15:26.320 align:middle line:84%
is perfectly illustrated
by reliance on bees

00:15:26.320 --> 00:15:29.100 align:middle line:90%
and their pollination of plants.

00:15:29.100 --> 00:15:32.230 align:middle line:84%
It's hypothesized that
without bees life wouldn't

00:15:32.230 --> 00:15:34.450 align:middle line:90%
stand much of a chance.

00:15:34.450 --> 00:15:38.130 align:middle line:84%
Insect pollination is needed
for really all the things

00:15:38.130 --> 00:15:43.005 align:middle line:84%
that make eating interesting,
so all the fruits, the nuts,

00:15:43.005 --> 00:15:46.850 align:middle line:84%
and things like that all
require insect pollination

00:15:46.850 --> 00:15:49.065 align:middle line:84%
and bees are the most
important group of pollinators.

00:15:49.065 --> 00:16:05.640 align:middle line:90%


00:16:05.640 --> 00:16:08.571 align:middle line:10%
If the bees weren't here,
we'd have a very boring planet.

00:16:08.571 --> 00:16:09.270 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:16:09.270 --> 00:16:10.860 align:middle line:84%
We would have a
very thin existence,

00:16:10.860 --> 00:16:12.850 align:middle line:84%
I think that's the point
without bees and of course,

00:16:12.850 --> 00:16:15.860 align:middle line:84%
as well as the food
that way need to eat,

00:16:15.860 --> 00:16:18.520 align:middle line:84%
they're pollinating
wild plants as well.

00:16:18.520 --> 00:16:21.810 align:middle line:84%
And in many cases, we don't
know details about pollination

00:16:21.810 --> 00:16:23.870 align:middle line:84%
of wild plants
but we can be sure

00:16:23.870 --> 00:16:26.950 align:middle line:84%
that without bees to pollinate
then many of our wild plants

00:16:26.950 --> 00:16:27.659 align:middle line:90%
will disappear.

00:16:27.659 --> 00:16:45.263 align:middle line:90%


00:16:45.263 --> 00:16:48.340 align:middle line:84%
RADIO HOST (ON RADIO): We
are with Marianne Frazier,

00:16:48.340 --> 00:16:51.190 align:middle line:84%
the senior extension associate
for beekeeping at Pennsylvania

00:16:51.190 --> 00:16:53.180 align:middle line:90%
State University.

00:16:53.180 --> 00:16:56.320 align:middle line:10%
What are the classic criteria
of colony collapse disorder

00:16:56.320 --> 00:16:59.580 align:middle line:10%
so that any beekeeper can go
out there and look at their bees

00:16:59.580 --> 00:17:03.327 align:middle line:10%
and say, this looks like a
pretty classic case of this?

00:17:03.327 --> 00:17:04.660 align:middle line:10%
MARYANN FRAZIER (ON
RADIO): The symptoms

00:17:04.660 --> 00:17:10.180 align:middle line:10%
are that the bees are
relatively healthy and strong

00:17:10.180 --> 00:17:13.099 align:middle line:10%
and in a very short
period of time,

00:17:13.099 --> 00:17:16.079 align:middle line:10%
the adult bee population
disappears from the colony.

00:17:16.079 --> 00:17:17.490 align:middle line:90%
It leaves the colony.

00:17:17.490 --> 00:17:19.760 align:middle line:84%
And what it leaves
behind is a lot of brood,

00:17:19.760 --> 00:17:23.374 align:middle line:84%
meaning the young
bees, honey and pollen.

00:17:23.374 --> 00:17:24.740 align:middle line:10%
RADIO HOST (ON RADIO):
On what continents

00:17:24.740 --> 00:17:27.650 align:middle line:10%
has this colony collapse
disorder been observed?

00:17:27.650 --> 00:17:30.700 align:middle line:84%
MARYANN FRAZIER (ON RADIO):
Well the decline of honeybees

00:17:30.700 --> 00:17:36.270 align:middle line:90%
has occurred actually worldwide.

00:17:36.270 --> 00:17:41.030 align:middle line:84%
We've seen many other countries
report declines in honeybees,

00:17:41.030 --> 00:17:44.190 align:middle line:84%
whether or not it's truly due
to this thing called colony

00:17:44.190 --> 00:17:50.048 align:middle line:84%
collapse disorder, which is a
pretty unique set of criteria

00:17:50.048 --> 00:17:51.107 align:middle line:90%
is another question.

00:17:51.107 --> 00:17:52.240 align:middle line:84%
And that's one of
the things we're

00:17:52.240 --> 00:17:54.440 align:middle line:84%
trying to understand by
trying to communicate

00:17:54.440 --> 00:17:58.210 align:middle line:84%
with other people in
other parts of the world.

00:17:58.210 --> 00:17:59.980 align:middle line:10%
This sort of current
concern particularly

00:17:59.980 --> 00:18:03.490 align:middle line:10%
dates from about
2006 and particularly

00:18:03.490 --> 00:18:07.030 align:middle line:10%
in the United States where a
lot of commercial bee keepers

00:18:07.030 --> 00:18:10.220 align:middle line:10%
suddenly found that their
bees had been healthy

00:18:10.220 --> 00:18:12.400 align:middle line:10%
at one point in the year
and then in late summer

00:18:12.400 --> 00:18:15.440 align:middle line:10%
just suffered these
spectacular losses.

00:18:15.440 --> 00:18:17.970 align:middle line:84%
And they appeared to be
different from anything

00:18:17.970 --> 00:18:19.150 align:middle line:90%
that had been seen before.

00:18:19.150 --> 00:18:21.240 align:middle line:84%
So people were just
going to their hives

00:18:21.240 --> 00:18:24.015 align:middle line:84%
and finding there
were no bees at all.

00:18:24.015 --> 00:18:27.140 align:middle line:84%
NARRATOR: Colony collapse
disorder has affected hives

00:18:27.140 --> 00:18:30.240 align:middle line:84%
all around the world
with some countries

00:18:30.240 --> 00:18:33.600 align:middle line:90%
reporting losses of up to 70%.

00:18:33.600 --> 00:18:37.590 align:middle line:10%
A variety of reasons have
been offered as to its cause,

00:18:37.590 --> 00:18:40.330 align:middle line:10%
but none of them have been
able to conclusively explain

00:18:40.330 --> 00:18:44.920 align:middle line:10%
why all of a sudden bees
don't return to the hives,

00:18:44.920 --> 00:18:48.410 align:middle line:10%
apart from one, a
sensational piece of research

00:18:48.410 --> 00:18:50.970 align:middle line:10%
by Joseph Kuhn and his team.

00:18:50.970 --> 00:18:54.380 align:middle line:84%
In an experiment, the doctor
worked with eight beehives

00:18:54.380 --> 00:18:58.450 align:middle line:84%
and placed a regular home deck
phone inside half of them.

00:18:58.450 --> 00:19:01.550 align:middle line:84%
The scientists then monitored
if the presence of a deck phone

00:19:01.550 --> 00:19:04.910 align:middle line:84%
would affect the way that
bees return to their hive.

00:19:04.910 --> 00:19:06.555 align:middle line:90%
The results were astonishing.

00:19:06.555 --> 00:19:09.750 align:middle line:90%


00:19:09.750 --> 00:19:12.090 align:middle line:84%
In the hives where no
deck phone was present,

00:19:12.090 --> 00:19:17.340 align:middle line:84%
the bees returned
at a normal rate,

00:19:17.340 --> 00:19:19.580 align:middle line:84%
but in the hives which
contained a deck phone,

00:19:19.580 --> 00:19:20.890 align:middle line:90%
the bees hardly returned at all.

00:19:20.890 --> 00:19:23.900 align:middle line:90%


00:19:23.900 --> 00:19:26.020 align:middle line:10%
In one hive containing
a deck phone,

00:19:26.020 --> 00:19:29.500 align:middle line:10%
not a single bee returned.

00:19:29.500 --> 00:19:30.850 align:middle line:84%
To fully understand
the relevance

00:19:30.850 --> 00:19:33.640 align:middle line:84%
of Dr. Kuhn's experiment,
we must first understand

00:19:33.640 --> 00:19:36.270 align:middle line:90%
how a deck phone works.

00:19:36.270 --> 00:19:38.170 align:middle line:84%
The reason you are able
to walk around your home

00:19:38.170 --> 00:19:41.080 align:middle line:84%
talking on your deck phone
is because the base station

00:19:41.080 --> 00:19:43.620 align:middle line:84%
of the direct phone sends
electromagnetic frequency

00:19:43.620 --> 00:19:45.764 align:middle line:84%
waves called microwaves
to the handset.

00:19:45.764 --> 00:19:49.860 align:middle line:90%


00:19:49.860 --> 00:19:51.870 align:middle line:84%
This is exactly the same
way that a mobile phone

00:19:51.870 --> 00:19:54.190 align:middle line:84%
mast communicates
with a mobile phone.

00:19:54.190 --> 00:19:59.770 align:middle line:90%


00:19:59.770 --> 00:20:02.540 align:middle line:84%
A deck phone is basically
a miniature version

00:20:02.540 --> 00:20:03.725 align:middle line:90%
of a mobile phone mast.

00:20:03.725 --> 00:20:15.540 align:middle line:90%


00:20:15.540 --> 00:20:18.560 align:middle line:84%
If a bee is affected by what
comes out of a deck phone,

00:20:18.560 --> 00:20:20.910 align:middle line:84%
it will most definitely
be affected by what comes

00:20:20.910 --> 00:20:22.150 align:middle line:90%
out of a mobile phone mast.

00:20:22.150 --> 00:20:28.830 align:middle line:90%


00:20:28.830 --> 00:20:31.980 align:middle line:84%
And with four billion mobile
phone users around the world,

00:20:31.980 --> 00:20:34.030 align:middle line:84%
all of a sudden there
are an awful lot

00:20:34.030 --> 00:20:35.150 align:middle line:90%
of mobile phone masts.

00:20:35.150 --> 00:20:44.450 align:middle line:90%


00:20:44.450 --> 00:20:46.440 align:middle line:84%
The bee's magnetic
sense allows it

00:20:46.440 --> 00:20:50.820 align:middle line:84%
to navigate using the magnetic
lines of the Earth, an ability

00:20:50.820 --> 00:20:55.580 align:middle line:84%
it has spent millions of years
you fine tuning and developing.

00:20:55.580 --> 00:20:59.060 align:middle line:84%
Does it stand to reason then
that such an acute sensitivity

00:20:59.060 --> 00:21:00.640 align:middle line:84%
will be affected by
even the slightest

00:21:00.640 --> 00:21:04.690 align:middle line:84%
change in the
electromagnetic environment?

00:21:04.690 --> 00:21:08.060 align:middle line:84%
So what about a gargantuan
change and one which

00:21:08.060 --> 00:21:09.725 align:middle line:90%
has happened almost overnight?

00:21:09.725 --> 00:21:14.790 align:middle line:90%


00:21:14.790 --> 00:21:17.100 align:middle line:84%
Are there other species
that have this sensitivity

00:21:17.100 --> 00:21:20.080 align:middle line:84%
to magnetic fields,
a sensitivity

00:21:20.080 --> 00:21:22.805 align:middle line:84%
which ultimately makes
them vulnerable to man-made

00:21:22.805 --> 00:21:23.504 align:middle line:90%
frequencies?

00:21:23.504 --> 00:21:26.110 align:middle line:90%


00:21:26.110 --> 00:21:29.110 align:middle line:84%
Unfortunately, the discovery
of a new protein cell

00:21:29.110 --> 00:21:32.910 align:middle line:84%
called a cryptochrome suggests
all life has a magnetic sense.

00:21:32.910 --> 00:21:44.830 align:middle line:90%


00:21:44.830 --> 00:21:48.500 align:middle line:84%
They were discovered
in the 1990s in plants

00:21:48.500 --> 00:21:52.090 align:middle line:84%
where their function is to
absorb blue light, which

00:21:52.090 --> 00:21:54.350 align:middle line:90%
is used to regulate growth.

00:21:54.350 --> 00:21:59.660 align:middle line:84%
They were since been found
in insects, animals, mammals,

00:21:59.660 --> 00:22:01.680 align:middle line:90%
including humans and in birds.

00:22:01.680 --> 00:22:07.740 align:middle line:10%
Cryptochromes are a biological
molecule called a protein.

00:22:07.740 --> 00:22:13.790 align:middle line:10%
It's generated by some of
your genes called cry genes

00:22:13.790 --> 00:22:15.940 align:middle line:10%
and the cryptochrome
molecule actually

00:22:15.940 --> 00:22:19.640 align:middle line:10%
controls your circadian
rhythms including

00:22:19.640 --> 00:22:21.170 align:middle line:10%
melatonin productions.

00:22:21.170 --> 00:22:24.075 align:middle line:84%
Some of the cryptochrome seem
to have a function of absorbing

00:22:24.075 --> 00:22:28.450 align:middle line:84%
the light as detectors
for the circadian clock,

00:22:28.450 --> 00:22:32.860 align:middle line:84%
so they are inputs for
the light-dark cycle

00:22:32.860 --> 00:22:37.715 align:middle line:84%
that many species seem to have,
plants as well as animals.

00:22:37.715 --> 00:22:42.250 align:middle line:90%


00:22:42.250 --> 00:22:45.230 align:middle line:10%
NARRATOR: But in the
year 2000, Thorsten Ritz

00:22:45.230 --> 00:22:47.000 align:middle line:10%
demonstrated an
even more amazing

00:22:47.000 --> 00:22:49.800 align:middle line:10%
role for the cryptochrome.

00:22:49.800 --> 00:22:52.160 align:middle line:84%
In a series of
experiments on Robbins,

00:22:52.160 --> 00:22:55.290 align:middle line:84%
he demonstrated that their
navigational sense was not only

00:22:55.290 --> 00:22:57.490 align:middle line:84%
a magnetic one, but
it came directly

00:22:57.490 --> 00:22:59.600 align:middle line:84%
from the cryptochrome
cells, which

00:22:59.600 --> 00:23:02.310 align:middle line:90%
are located behind the eye.

00:23:02.310 --> 00:23:06.290 align:middle line:10%
I think the Ritz
paper published in 2000

00:23:06.290 --> 00:23:09.700 align:middle line:10%
is one of those
milestones in science

00:23:09.700 --> 00:23:12.760 align:middle line:10%
because he proposed that this
cryptochrome molecule, which,

00:23:12.760 --> 00:23:16.300 align:middle line:10%
remember, is best known for its
effect in controlling circadian

00:23:16.300 --> 00:23:19.410 align:middle line:10%
rhythms, that that
molecule was actually

00:23:19.410 --> 00:23:22.330 align:middle line:10%
responsible for giving
the magnetic compass

00:23:22.330 --> 00:23:24.535 align:middle line:10%
information in birds.

00:23:24.535 --> 00:23:27.930 align:middle line:84%
The birds literally see
the Earth's magnetic field

00:23:27.930 --> 00:23:31.890 align:middle line:84%
perhaps as a bright or
dark spot superimposed

00:23:31.890 --> 00:23:34.050 align:middle line:90%
on their field of vision.

00:23:34.050 --> 00:23:36.750 align:middle line:84%
Then as they then move their
head or their body around,

00:23:36.750 --> 00:23:40.070 align:middle line:84%
the spot moves and so rather
like a heads-up display

00:23:40.070 --> 00:23:41.860 align:middle line:90%
for a fighter pilot.

00:23:41.860 --> 00:23:46.430 align:middle line:84%
They have this thing that
they see, goodness knows

00:23:46.430 --> 00:23:48.850 align:middle line:84%
what it would be,
which allows them

00:23:48.850 --> 00:23:52.270 align:middle line:90%
to orient while they're flying.

00:23:52.270 --> 00:23:57.100 align:middle line:84%
The way he tested that was to
expose birds to radio frequency

00:23:57.100 --> 00:23:59.810 align:middle line:84%
fields to see if it
actually disturbed

00:23:59.810 --> 00:24:03.620 align:middle line:84%
their magnetic compass and not
only did the radio frequency

00:24:03.620 --> 00:24:09.160 align:middle line:84%
field indeed disrupt the
migration of Robbins,

00:24:09.160 --> 00:24:12.990 align:middle line:84%
but it did so at very, very
low intensities of fields

00:24:12.990 --> 00:24:15.745 align:middle line:84%
and that's really important
and really interesting,

00:24:15.745 --> 00:24:19.700 align:middle line:84%
that very low level radio
frequency fields interfered

00:24:19.700 --> 00:24:23.570 align:middle line:90%
with the Robbin's compass.

00:24:23.570 --> 00:24:26.960 align:middle line:10%
NARRATOR: The experiments
by Ritz clearly demonstrated

00:24:26.960 --> 00:24:29.330 align:middle line:10%
that the cryptochrome
cell used in navigation

00:24:29.330 --> 00:24:32.830 align:middle line:10%
was seriously affected
by man-made frequencies

00:24:32.830 --> 00:24:36.440 align:middle line:10%
and man-made frequencies levels
well below those deemed safe

00:24:36.440 --> 00:24:39.430 align:middle line:10%
by the governing body ICNIRP.

00:24:39.430 --> 00:24:42.210 align:middle line:10%
All of the animal
navigation studies,

00:24:42.210 --> 00:24:46.800 align:middle line:10%
the cockroaches, the zebra
finches, the chickens,

00:24:46.800 --> 00:24:51.470 align:middle line:10%
the Robbins, they've all
had their magnetic compass

00:24:51.470 --> 00:24:54.180 align:middle line:10%
disturbed by radio
frequency fields

00:24:54.180 --> 00:24:57.440 align:middle line:10%
well below the ICNIRP
public exposure limit.

00:24:57.440 --> 00:25:00.010 align:middle line:90%


00:25:00.010 --> 00:25:04.340 align:middle line:84%
I work on birds, particularly
birds and insects.

00:25:04.340 --> 00:25:06.950 align:middle line:10%
I have shown that they
are sensitive to fields

00:25:06.950 --> 00:25:10.850 align:middle line:10%
way below the ICNIRP levels
that claim are safe for us.

00:25:10.850 --> 00:25:12.780 align:middle line:10%
If you look at where
the research shows

00:25:12.780 --> 00:25:15.740 align:middle line:10%
they are sensitive to, there's
good stuff in the literature

00:25:15.740 --> 00:25:19.127 align:middle line:10%
showing it's significantly lower
than what we are allowed to be

00:25:19.127 --> 00:25:20.360 align:middle line:10%
exposed to and
therefore what they're

00:25:20.360 --> 00:25:22.940 align:middle line:10%
exposed to in the environment.

00:25:22.940 --> 00:25:25.610 align:middle line:84%
There's certainly
solid scientific reason

00:25:25.610 --> 00:25:28.320 align:middle line:84%
for supposing that
magnetic fields,

00:25:28.320 --> 00:25:32.290 align:middle line:84%
artificial magnetic fields,
will disturb the habitat

00:25:32.290 --> 00:25:33.185 align:middle line:90%
of a number of species.

00:25:33.185 --> 00:26:49.696 align:middle line:90%


00:26:49.696 --> 00:26:51.480 align:middle line:84%
How much has our
environment changed

00:26:51.480 --> 00:26:53.460 align:middle line:84%
because of electromagnetic
fields because of--

00:26:53.460 --> 00:26:56.800 align:middle line:84%
Over the last 25 years, it's
a changed beyond recognition,

00:26:56.800 --> 00:26:57.600 align:middle line:90%
just beyond recognition.

00:26:57.600 --> 00:27:00.630 align:middle line:84%
It's millions and
millions of times in terms

00:27:00.630 --> 00:27:02.540 align:middle line:90%
of electromagnetic energy.

00:27:02.540 --> 00:27:06.030 align:middle line:10%
The former National
Radiological Protection Board,

00:27:06.030 --> 00:27:08.960 align:middle line:10%
in one of their documents,
said that they thought

00:27:08.960 --> 00:27:12.920 align:middle line:10%
that the radiation environment,
if you like to call it that,

00:27:12.920 --> 00:27:17.260 align:middle line:10%
had increased many millions of
times from what it was 50 years

00:27:17.260 --> 00:27:19.740 align:middle line:10%
ago, many millions of times.

00:27:19.740 --> 00:27:22.900 align:middle line:84%
It's an enormous change
in environment on Earth,

00:27:22.900 --> 00:27:25.000 align:middle line:84%
I mean, completely swamped
all these natural signals,

00:27:25.000 --> 00:27:27.757 align:middle line:84%
including the Schumann waves
that we have evolved with.

00:27:27.757 --> 00:27:41.180 align:middle line:90%


00:27:41.180 --> 00:27:44.220 align:middle line:84%
One of the reasons that
cryptochromes are particularly

00:27:44.220 --> 00:27:48.890 align:middle line:84%
interesting from the point of
view of human being detecting

00:27:48.890 --> 00:27:53.640 align:middle line:84%
magnetic fields is that there's
a recent study by Dr. Foley

00:27:53.640 --> 00:27:58.800 align:middle line:84%
and colleagues showing that
if you put human cryptochromes

00:27:58.800 --> 00:28:04.070 align:middle line:84%
into the fruit fly, then the
fruit fly is made particularly

00:28:04.070 --> 00:28:06.530 align:middle line:84%
sensitive because
of the presence

00:28:06.530 --> 00:28:08.570 align:middle line:90%
of these human cryptochromes.

00:28:08.570 --> 00:28:13.920 align:middle line:90%


00:28:13.920 --> 00:28:17.430 align:middle line:84%
So this is actually showing
that human cryptochromes

00:28:17.430 --> 00:28:19.570 align:middle line:90%
are magnetically sensitive.

00:28:19.570 --> 00:28:21.672 align:middle line:84%
In fact, they detect
magnetic fields.

00:28:21.672 --> 00:28:26.506 align:middle line:90%


00:28:26.506 --> 00:28:28.700 align:middle line:84%
NARRATOR: The discovery
of the cryptochrome cell

00:28:28.700 --> 00:28:32.900 align:middle line:84%
has sparked new interest in the
magnetic sense of man, a sense

00:28:32.900 --> 00:28:35.680 align:middle line:84%
that Robin Baker had
predicted some 40 years ago.

00:28:35.680 --> 00:28:38.760 align:middle line:90%


00:28:38.760 --> 00:28:40.060 align:middle line:84%
NARRATOR (ON TV):
This is not some kind

00:28:40.060 --> 00:28:42.230 align:middle line:90%
of scientific blind man's bluff.

00:28:42.230 --> 00:28:44.380 align:middle line:84%
It's an experiment to
find out whether children

00:28:44.380 --> 00:28:46.420 align:middle line:90%
have a sense of direction.

00:28:46.420 --> 00:28:48.490 align:middle line:84%
Blindfolded and ear
muffed, the subject

00:28:48.490 --> 00:28:50.520 align:middle line:84%
is turned around
in a special chair

00:28:50.520 --> 00:28:53.350 align:middle line:84%
until he can't remember
which direction he's facing.

00:28:53.350 --> 00:28:56.260 align:middle line:84%
The chair stops and the subject
guesses whether he's facing

00:28:56.260 --> 00:29:00.080 align:middle line:90%
east, west, north or south.

00:29:00.080 --> 00:29:02.720 align:middle line:84%
The guest is recorded
in a small computer.

00:29:02.720 --> 00:29:04.910 align:middle line:84%
If children have no
sense of direction,

00:29:04.910 --> 00:29:06.650 align:middle line:90%
their guesses would be random.

00:29:06.650 --> 00:29:07.670 align:middle line:90%
But they're not.

00:29:07.670 --> 00:29:10.070 align:middle line:84%
Children after the
age of about 10 or 11

00:29:10.070 --> 00:29:11.660 align:middle line:90%
make pretty good guesses.

00:29:11.660 --> 00:29:14.370 align:middle line:84%
It seems they have a
real sense of direction

00:29:14.370 --> 00:29:16.880 align:middle line:84%
and it seems to be
a magnetic sense.

00:29:16.880 --> 00:29:19.900 align:middle line:84%
When the scientist struck a
magnet to the subject's head,

00:29:19.900 --> 00:29:21.830 align:middle line:84%
it disrupts his sense
of direction severely.

00:29:21.830 --> 00:29:24.420 align:middle line:90%


00:29:24.420 --> 00:29:26.720 align:middle line:84%
And this is a huge
advance in understanding.

00:29:26.720 --> 00:29:28.660 align:middle line:90%
It begs all sorts of questions.

00:29:28.660 --> 00:29:30.860 align:middle line:84%
It begs questions of
whether human beings

00:29:30.860 --> 00:29:33.450 align:middle line:84%
can actually navigate in
the Earth's magnetic field.

00:29:33.450 --> 00:29:36.200 align:middle line:84%
Even though they don't
do it today, did they

00:29:36.200 --> 00:29:39.130 align:middle line:90%
do it thousands of years ago.

00:29:39.130 --> 00:29:41.580 align:middle line:84%
And of course, it begs the
question as to whether this was

00:29:41.580 --> 00:29:46.580 align:middle line:84%
a process by which magnetic
fields are actually detected

00:29:46.580 --> 00:29:49.450 align:middle line:84%
in the human body, which
leads to this disturbance

00:29:49.450 --> 00:29:52.860 align:middle line:84%
of circadian rhythms which would
explain all the diverse health

00:29:52.860 --> 00:29:57.130 align:middle line:84%
effects that we see so much else
in the epidemiological studies

00:29:57.130 --> 00:29:59.289 align:middle line:90%
of health in magnetic fields.

00:29:59.289 --> 00:30:03.546 align:middle line:90%


00:30:03.546 --> 00:30:05.470 align:middle line:84%
NARRATOR: If mankind
has the ability

00:30:05.470 --> 00:30:09.820 align:middle line:84%
to sense magnetic
fields, the same ability

00:30:09.820 --> 00:30:15.170 align:middle line:84%
as the bees, the birds,
and the butterflies,

00:30:15.170 --> 00:30:17.660 align:middle line:84%
does that also mean that we
are as vulnerable as they

00:30:17.660 --> 00:30:20.830 align:middle line:90%
are to man-made frequencies?

00:30:20.830 --> 00:30:24.200 align:middle line:84%
Will changes in our
environment affect us

00:30:24.200 --> 00:30:25.722 align:middle line:90%
as it's clearly affecting them?

00:30:25.722 --> 00:30:35.740 align:middle line:90%


00:30:35.740 --> 00:30:38.305 align:middle line:84%
INTERVIEWER: So how would
describe electrosensitivity?

00:30:38.305 --> 00:30:41.400 align:middle line:90%


00:30:41.400 --> 00:30:44.480 align:middle line:84%
Electrical sensitivity is
when people start reacting,

00:30:44.480 --> 00:30:48.220 align:middle line:84%
their body starts reacting
to electromagnetic fields.

00:30:48.220 --> 00:30:49.880 align:middle line:10%
Generally speaking, the
electromagnetic fields

00:30:49.880 --> 00:30:52.020 align:middle line:10%
that they'll be
reacting to is wireless.

00:30:52.020 --> 00:30:53.810 align:middle line:10%
So it will be wireless
communications.

00:30:53.810 --> 00:30:55.340 align:middle line:90%
It will be Wi-Fi.

00:30:55.340 --> 00:31:04.600 align:middle line:84%
It will be cordless phones, deck
phones, mobile phones, masts,

00:31:04.600 --> 00:31:09.860 align:middle line:84%
all of them emitting
signals that our body

00:31:09.860 --> 00:31:11.537 align:middle line:90%
has never experienced before.

00:31:11.537 --> 00:31:14.340 align:middle line:90%


00:31:14.340 --> 00:31:19.580 align:middle line:84%
And when people start to become
affected, the way I became

00:31:19.580 --> 00:31:22.260 align:middle line:84%
infected, the way that
it starts to affect you

00:31:22.260 --> 00:31:24.450 align:middle line:84%
is generally speaking
it's your head first

00:31:24.450 --> 00:31:27.770 align:middle line:84%
and it will start giving
you pains in your head.

00:31:27.770 --> 00:31:31.420 align:middle line:84%
I hate to use the word headache
because it's pains in your head

00:31:31.420 --> 00:31:33.810 align:middle line:84%
that is unlike
any other headache

00:31:33.810 --> 00:31:35.146 align:middle line:90%
you've ever had before.

00:31:35.146 --> 00:31:37.810 align:middle line:90%


00:31:37.810 --> 00:31:42.770 align:middle line:10%
Most people's complaints are
things like cardiac arrhythmia,

00:31:42.770 --> 00:31:48.340 align:middle line:10%
insomnia, headache, visual
disturbance, vertigo,

00:31:48.340 --> 00:31:52.420 align:middle line:10%
different kinds of
paresthesias or neurasthenias

00:31:52.420 --> 00:31:55.530 align:middle line:10%
where they are feeling unusual
sensations within their body.

00:31:55.530 --> 00:31:59.500 align:middle line:90%


00:31:59.500 --> 00:32:01.880 align:middle line:84%
But really it can also
affect endocrine function,

00:32:01.880 --> 00:32:07.150 align:middle line:84%
thyroid function, again,
the list is really endless.

00:32:07.150 --> 00:32:10.600 align:middle line:84%
In my particular case, and
this is not everybody's case,

00:32:10.600 --> 00:32:12.830 align:middle line:84%
if I then don't get
out of the environment,

00:32:12.830 --> 00:32:16.540 align:middle line:84%
I start getting quite
severe pains in my gut

00:32:16.540 --> 00:32:19.650 align:middle line:84%
and that will then
mean it's too late.

00:32:19.650 --> 00:32:21.080 align:middle line:84%
I will then start
bleeding internally.

00:32:21.080 --> 00:32:24.370 align:middle line:90%


00:32:24.370 --> 00:32:26.650 align:middle line:84%
I think that the
symptoms are so diverse

00:32:26.650 --> 00:32:29.920 align:middle line:84%
and the associations
that people make

00:32:29.920 --> 00:32:32.910 align:middle line:84%
are very difficult
to accept if you have

00:32:32.910 --> 00:32:34.340 align:middle line:84%
no knowledge of
this subject, which

00:32:34.340 --> 00:32:38.240 align:middle line:84%
most physicians do not have and
that's no fault of their own.

00:32:38.240 --> 00:32:40.410 align:middle line:84%
We're not trained to
recognize this condition.

00:32:40.410 --> 00:32:43.820 align:middle line:84%
It's very innovative and
our understanding of it

00:32:43.820 --> 00:32:45.440 align:middle line:84%
is entirely embryonic
at this stage.

00:32:45.440 --> 00:32:48.170 align:middle line:84%
We're at the very first
steps of unraveling and fully

00:32:48.170 --> 00:32:49.440 align:middle line:90%
understanding this condition.

00:32:49.440 --> 00:32:53.940 align:middle line:90%


00:32:53.940 --> 00:32:56.220 align:middle line:84%
NARRATOR: Brian,
like many sufferers

00:32:56.220 --> 00:32:58.830 align:middle line:84%
of electrosensitivity,
has been forced to make

00:32:58.830 --> 00:33:00.748 align:middle line:90%
radical changes to his home.

00:33:00.748 --> 00:33:06.090 align:middle line:84%
The area of these two
rooms have been completely

00:33:06.090 --> 00:33:16.290 align:middle line:84%
shielded in metal foil so
that this room and the bedroom

00:33:16.290 --> 00:33:18.520 align:middle line:90%
are a Faraday cage.

00:33:18.520 --> 00:33:25.840 align:middle line:84%
And if you actually check
the electromagnetic fields

00:33:25.840 --> 00:33:30.270 align:middle line:84%
or the microwave, and this
machine is simply converting

00:33:30.270 --> 00:33:36.360 align:middle line:84%
microwaves to no use, you
find that the mast that's was

00:33:36.360 --> 00:33:40.240 align:middle line:84%
about half a mile away
over there, which causes me

00:33:40.240 --> 00:33:47.560 align:middle line:84%
a problem, by shielding the room
and putting metalized glass,

00:33:47.560 --> 00:33:53.410 align:middle line:84%
means that I can eliminate most
of the electromagnetic fields.

00:33:53.410 --> 00:33:58.800 align:middle line:84%
The aspects of an organism that
allow it to detect and respond

00:33:58.800 --> 00:34:04.660 align:middle line:84%
to electromagnetic fields, you
could say this way it's going

00:34:04.660 --> 00:34:05.990 align:middle line:84%
to use a number of
different contacts

00:34:05.990 --> 00:34:08.550 align:middle line:84%
and if you bisect it and
break it down, electrically

00:34:08.550 --> 00:34:11.830 align:middle line:84%
sensitive, you could
say that really that's

00:34:11.830 --> 00:34:14.550 align:middle line:84%
a response to life
itself in that,

00:34:14.550 --> 00:34:16.929 align:middle line:84%
for example, if we are
looking at an organism

00:34:16.929 --> 00:34:19.350 align:middle line:84%
to determine the
presence of life,

00:34:19.350 --> 00:34:21.860 align:middle line:84%
we're really looking for
the presence of electricity.

00:34:21.860 --> 00:34:24.639 align:middle line:84%
So with the electrocardiogram,
for example, the ECG

00:34:24.639 --> 00:34:26.469 align:middle line:84%
and the electroencephalogram,
the EEG,

00:34:26.469 --> 00:34:28.469 align:middle line:84%
what we're looking at
there is the presence

00:34:28.469 --> 00:34:30.780 align:middle line:84%
of electricity from
those target organs,

00:34:30.780 --> 00:34:32.460 align:middle line:90%
the brain and the heart.

00:34:32.460 --> 00:34:35.179 align:middle line:84%
And when we see the
presence of that,

00:34:35.179 --> 00:34:37.730 align:middle line:84%
that's a sign that
there is life.

00:34:37.730 --> 00:34:41.250 align:middle line:10%
So in a way, given that
on a cellular level,

00:34:41.250 --> 00:34:43.770 align:middle line:10%
electromagnetic
fields, a part of life

00:34:43.770 --> 00:34:45.780 align:middle line:10%
itself, we could
say that all life is

00:34:45.780 --> 00:34:48.700 align:middle line:10%
electromagnetically sensitive.

00:34:48.700 --> 00:34:52.010 align:middle line:84%
NARRATOR: Desperate to convince
people that electrosensitivity

00:34:52.010 --> 00:34:55.500 align:middle line:84%
was genuine, Brian and a
number of other sufferers

00:34:55.500 --> 00:35:00.560 align:middle line:84%
signed up to a landmark
experiment at Essex University.

00:35:00.560 --> 00:35:03.250 align:middle line:84%
The experiment,
run by Elaine Fox,

00:35:03.250 --> 00:35:05.878 align:middle line:84%
would suddenly become the
definitive work on the subject.

00:35:05.878 --> 00:35:11.870 align:middle line:90%


00:35:11.870 --> 00:35:14.500 align:middle line:84%
You have to go
into a shielded room

00:35:14.500 --> 00:35:17.490 align:middle line:84%
and you go in there for a
relatively short period of time

00:35:17.490 --> 00:35:20.740 align:middle line:84%
and the mast is on for 10
minutes and off for 10 minutes

00:35:20.740 --> 00:35:23.890 align:middle line:84%
and on for 10 minutes and
to see whether you can

00:35:23.890 --> 00:35:26.440 align:middle line:90%
detect whether it's on or not.

00:35:26.440 --> 00:35:29.120 align:middle line:84%
And I went into the
room having told them

00:35:29.120 --> 00:35:32.020 align:middle line:84%
that I would not be able to
tell them whether the mast was

00:35:32.020 --> 00:35:33.670 align:middle line:90%
on or off or on.

00:35:33.670 --> 00:35:35.080 align:middle line:90%
INTERVIEWER: Why's that?

00:35:35.080 --> 00:35:41.610 align:middle line:84%
Because their understanding of
how you react to this is wrong.

00:35:41.610 --> 00:35:44.130 align:middle line:84%
This is not a case
with most people

00:35:44.130 --> 00:35:48.740 align:middle line:84%
where you turn the mast
on and oh, I'm affected.

00:35:48.740 --> 00:35:50.560 align:middle line:84%
They turn the mast
off, oh, I'm OK again.

00:35:50.560 --> 00:35:52.090 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't work like that.

00:35:52.090 --> 00:35:55.260 align:middle line:84%
I suffer with hay fever
and when I go into a field

00:35:55.260 --> 00:35:57.310 align:middle line:84%
where there is pollen,
it takes a while

00:35:57.310 --> 00:36:00.490 align:middle line:84%
before I'll be affected,
but it takes a long time

00:36:00.490 --> 00:36:01.680 align:middle line:90%
before I'm not affected.

00:36:01.680 --> 00:36:06.490 align:middle line:84%
I can be removed from the
hay field for 24 hours,

00:36:06.490 --> 00:36:08.960 align:middle line:84%
but I'll still be
feeling my hay fever

00:36:08.960 --> 00:36:11.290 align:middle line:84%
and electrical sensitivity
with most people

00:36:11.290 --> 00:36:12.952 align:middle line:90%
is a little bit like that.

00:36:12.952 --> 00:36:15.700 align:middle line:84%
NARRATOR: The way the team had
sets up the experiment meant

00:36:15.700 --> 00:36:17.560 align:middle line:84%
it would be almost
impossible for Brian

00:36:17.560 --> 00:36:21.480 align:middle line:84%
and the other volunteers to
prove they were being affected,

00:36:21.480 --> 00:36:23.820 align:middle line:84%
not that it would
matter as the team had

00:36:23.820 --> 00:36:27.080 align:middle line:84%
inexplicably decided to do
away with any form of vetting

00:36:27.080 --> 00:36:29.440 align:middle line:90%
procedure.

00:36:29.440 --> 00:36:31.860 align:middle line:84%
For one thing,
people appear to be

00:36:31.860 --> 00:36:33.210 align:middle line:90%
sensitive to different things.

00:36:33.210 --> 00:36:35.830 align:middle line:10%
I'm sensitive to
3G mobile phones.

00:36:35.830 --> 00:36:37.990 align:middle line:10%
I'm sensitive to
GSM mobile phones.

00:36:37.990 --> 00:36:40.210 align:middle line:10%
For example, there are
differences in the way

00:36:40.210 --> 00:36:41.330 align:middle line:10%
the modulation works.

00:36:41.330 --> 00:36:44.220 align:middle line:10%
I have no idea whether they're
right in their sensitivities,

00:36:44.220 --> 00:36:46.010 align:middle line:10%
but if that is the case,
then it makes sense

00:36:46.010 --> 00:36:48.370 align:middle line:10%
that the people who you've
gotten into your study

00:36:48.370 --> 00:36:50.360 align:middle line:10%
claim to be sensitive
to exactly the signal

00:36:50.360 --> 00:36:51.960 align:middle line:10%
that you're going to
be exposing them to.

00:36:51.960 --> 00:36:54.550 align:middle line:84%
If you have someone that,
for example, is always

00:36:54.550 --> 00:36:56.420 align:middle line:84%
sensitive to Wi-Fi
but they're never

00:36:56.420 --> 00:36:59.284 align:middle line:84%
sensitive to mobile
phones, if they exist,

00:36:59.284 --> 00:37:01.050 align:middle line:84%
then you make sure that what
they're being exposed to

00:37:01.050 --> 00:37:03.087 align:middle line:84%
is Wi-Fi and not mobile
phones because you're actually

00:37:03.087 --> 00:37:04.720 align:middle line:84%
trying to prove whether
they're sensitive to what

00:37:04.720 --> 00:37:05.740 align:middle line:90%
they're saying there are.

00:37:05.740 --> 00:37:07.560 align:middle line:84%
None of that
differentiation was done.

00:37:07.560 --> 00:37:09.420 align:middle line:84%
It was really if you claim
to be sensitive to anything

00:37:09.420 --> 00:37:12.980 align:middle line:84%
at all that happened to be
electromagnetic, you were in.

00:37:12.980 --> 00:37:16.670 align:middle line:10%
Well, one of the reasons why I
thought it was quite important

00:37:16.670 --> 00:37:20.590 align:middle line:10%
was I help people who are
electrically sensitive

00:37:20.590 --> 00:37:24.240 align:middle line:10%
and a couple of months before
