of an eight-year-old,

01:00:56.170 --> 01:00:59.820 align:middle line:90%
they would fail.

01:00:59.820 --> 01:01:02.340 align:middle line:84%
INTERVIEWER: Who is it
that sets the standards?

01:01:02.340 --> 01:01:06.930 align:middle line:84%
A group of people from a
committee called ICNIRP.

01:01:06.930 --> 01:01:12.477 align:middle line:90%


01:01:12.477 --> 01:01:16.440 align:middle line:10%
The people who do the
work on mobile phones

01:01:16.440 --> 01:01:19.500 align:middle line:10%
are by and large engineers.

01:01:19.500 --> 01:01:23.430 align:middle line:10%
They have no idea what is going
on inside the living cell,

01:01:23.430 --> 01:01:28.190 align:middle line:10%
but they are
pontificating on this.

01:01:28.190 --> 01:01:32.360 align:middle line:10%
They make the assumption that
the only thing that can affect

01:01:32.360 --> 01:01:35.990 align:middle line:10%
the well being of
a living organism

01:01:35.990 --> 01:01:40.431 align:middle line:10%
is if it is powerful
enough to heat the tissue.

01:01:40.431 --> 01:01:43.080 align:middle line:90%


01:01:43.080 --> 01:01:49.936 align:middle line:84%
Well, that's like saying we know
if we boil an egg it goes hard.

01:01:49.936 --> 01:01:55.020 align:middle line:84%
What they don't know is that
if they don't boil the egg,

01:01:55.020 --> 01:01:58.430 align:middle line:84%
it turns into a chicken
and haven't the slightest

01:01:58.430 --> 01:02:00.190 align:middle line:84%
idea how that
happens, but the yet

01:02:00.190 --> 01:02:02.830 align:middle line:90%
they pontificate as if they do.

01:02:02.830 --> 01:02:09.346 align:middle line:90%


01:02:09.346 --> 01:02:12.240 align:middle line:10%
NARRATOR: In 2011, the
World Health Organization

01:02:12.240 --> 01:02:18.340 align:middle line:10%
changed the danger rating of
mobile phones re-classing it

01:02:18.340 --> 01:02:24.890 align:middle line:10%
as possibly carcinogenic to
humans based on an increased

01:02:24.890 --> 01:02:29.600 align:middle line:10%
risk of contracting angioma, the
type of brain tumor associated

01:02:29.600 --> 01:02:32.840 align:middle line:10%
with using a mobile phone.

01:02:32.840 --> 01:02:35.138 align:middle line:84%
What was the catalyst for
this abrupt change in status?

01:02:35.138 --> 01:02:38.350 align:middle line:90%


01:02:38.350 --> 01:02:40.410 align:middle line:84%
There have been countless
studies conducted

01:02:40.410 --> 01:02:44.560 align:middle line:84%
into the possible health
effects of mobile phones,

01:02:44.560 --> 01:02:48.040 align:middle line:84%
some showing an effect,
some showing no effect.

01:02:48.040 --> 01:02:51.110 align:middle line:90%


01:02:51.110 --> 01:02:55.690 align:middle line:10%
But the most conclusive
came from Lennart Hardell.

01:02:55.690 --> 01:02:58.170 align:middle line:84%
He has overseen the largest
and most comprehensive piece

01:02:58.170 --> 01:03:01.590 align:middle line:84%
of research ever
conducted combining

01:03:01.590 --> 01:03:04.124 align:middle line:84%
his own work with that of
others from around the world.

01:03:04.124 --> 01:03:07.090 align:middle line:90%


01:03:07.090 --> 01:03:10.190 align:middle line:84%
From the early 1990s, they have
investigated the phone habits

01:03:10.190 --> 01:03:14.440 align:middle line:84%
of more than 2,000 people
from around the world, people

01:03:14.440 --> 01:03:20.960 align:middle line:84%
with tumors such as astrocytoma
and acoustic neuroma.

01:03:20.960 --> 01:03:23.440 align:middle line:84%
The brain tumors associated
most with mobile phone

01:03:23.440 --> 01:03:28.340 align:middle line:84%
use due to their
proximity to the air.

01:03:28.340 --> 01:03:30.372 align:middle line:90%
Their findings are shocking.

01:03:30.372 --> 01:03:33.270 align:middle line:90%


01:03:33.270 --> 01:03:36.710 align:middle line:84%
They concluded that mobile
phone use does increase

01:03:36.710 --> 01:03:42.330 align:middle line:84%
the risk of a brain
tumor and they also

01:03:42.330 --> 01:03:45.734 align:middle line:84%
discovered why earlier
research showed no effect.

01:03:45.734 --> 01:03:55.580 align:middle line:90%


01:03:55.580 --> 01:03:58.210 align:middle line:84%
I think there's more
evidence that it's

01:03:58.210 --> 01:04:02.310 align:middle line:84%
carcinogenic than just
possibly carcinogenic,

01:04:02.310 --> 01:04:07.040 align:middle line:84%
but I can understand it
in a way because most

01:04:07.040 --> 01:04:12.550 align:middle line:84%
of the cancers which will
arrive haven't arrived yet.

01:04:12.550 --> 01:04:15.210 align:middle line:84%
People haven't been
using cell phones

01:04:15.210 --> 01:04:21.658 align:middle line:84%
for long enough for the true
effect to become apparent.

01:04:21.658 --> 01:04:24.220 align:middle line:84%
NARRATOR: As is the case
with other carcinogens,

01:04:24.220 --> 01:04:26.720 align:middle line:84%
it takes at least 10 years
before you start to see

01:04:26.720 --> 01:04:29.570 align:middle line:90%
an effect from the exposure.

01:04:29.570 --> 01:04:31.540 align:middle line:84%
Because the mobile phone
explosion didn't really

01:04:31.540 --> 01:04:34.450 align:middle line:84%
take hold until the
late 1990s, it's

01:04:34.450 --> 01:04:36.100 align:middle line:84%
not surprising we
are just starting

01:04:36.100 --> 01:04:37.877 align:middle line:90%
to see the effects right now.

01:04:37.877 --> 01:04:41.150 align:middle line:90%


01:04:41.150 --> 01:04:42.770 align:middle line:84%
So what are the
telecoms industry

01:04:42.770 --> 01:04:48.750 align:middle line:84%
doing to protect its users
from contracting a brain tumor?

01:04:48.750 --> 01:04:55.510 align:middle line:84%
A flick to the far reaches
of their safety manuals

01:04:55.510 --> 01:04:57.230 align:middle line:84%
suggests that they
are more concerned

01:04:57.230 --> 01:04:58.400 align:middle line:90%
about protecting themselves.

01:04:58.400 --> 01:05:26.300 align:middle line:90%


01:05:26.300 --> 01:05:28.040 align:middle line:10%
At the back of almost
every single phone

01:05:28.040 --> 01:05:31.360 align:middle line:10%
user guide are instructions
on how far to keep your phone

01:05:31.360 --> 01:05:44.080 align:middle line:10%
from your body, instructions
which, in the most part,

01:05:44.080 --> 01:05:44.993 align:middle line:10%
are wholly unworkable.

01:05:44.993 --> 01:05:50.550 align:middle line:90%


01:05:50.550 --> 01:05:53.090 align:middle line:10%
And what happens when the
telecoms industry funds

01:05:53.090 --> 01:05:59.430 align:middle line:10%
research into the harm
that they are causing

01:05:59.430 --> 01:06:09.610 align:middle line:10%
and that research concludes that
there is an effect that the use

01:06:09.610 --> 01:06:11.860 align:middle line:10%
of a mobile phone
does play a role

01:06:11.860 --> 01:06:19.630 align:middle line:10%
in the development of
cancer, they tend to keep

01:06:19.630 --> 01:06:20.630 align:middle line:10%
that research to themselves.

01:06:20.630 --> 01:06:25.260 align:middle line:90%


01:06:25.260 --> 01:06:29.790 align:middle line:84%
We just don't know what
we're storing up with the MF

01:06:29.790 --> 01:06:33.460 align:middle line:84%
because the effects
are largely long term

01:06:33.460 --> 01:06:38.760 align:middle line:84%
and we have as you say
this ubiquitous exposure

01:06:38.760 --> 01:06:43.670 align:middle line:84%
and ubiquitous reliance
on these exposures.

01:06:43.670 --> 01:06:47.855 align:middle line:84%
We just don't fully understand
yet what we're doing.

01:06:47.855 --> 01:06:50.775 align:middle line:90%


01:06:50.775 --> 01:06:53.050 align:middle line:10%
NARRATOR: Although the
epidemiology clearly

01:06:53.050 --> 01:06:55.410 align:middle line:10%
shows that using a
mobile phone increases

01:06:55.410 --> 01:06:59.330 align:middle line:10%
the risk of contracting a brain
tumor, what people at ICNIRP

01:06:59.330 --> 01:07:03.610 align:middle line:10%
need to see is a definitive
cause and effect, how it

01:07:03.610 --> 01:07:07.560 align:middle line:10%
happens, what's
the mechanism, how

01:07:07.560 --> 01:07:11.780 align:middle line:10%
exactly is the cancer caused.

01:07:11.780 --> 01:07:16.010 align:middle line:10%
It may seem obvious that a
being so tuned in to the Earth's

01:07:16.010 --> 01:07:19.930 align:middle line:10%
frequencies and so sensitive
to her magnetic field

01:07:19.930 --> 01:07:22.740 align:middle line:10%
would naturally have a reaction
to man-made microwaves.

01:07:22.740 --> 01:07:26.320 align:middle line:90%


01:07:26.320 --> 01:07:28.960 align:middle line:84%
But for years, the
telecoms industry

01:07:28.960 --> 01:07:31.690 align:middle line:84%
have defended their actions
by asking the same question.

01:07:31.690 --> 01:07:34.450 align:middle line:90%


01:07:34.450 --> 01:07:37.670 align:middle line:84%
As it turns out, they've been
asking the wrong question.

01:07:37.670 --> 01:07:41.660 align:middle line:90%


01:07:41.660 --> 01:07:43.550 align:middle line:90%
The answer is melatonin.

01:07:43.550 --> 01:07:49.090 align:middle line:90%


01:07:49.090 --> 01:07:52.440 align:middle line:84%
You know melatonin is a
hormone and believe it or not,

01:07:52.440 --> 01:07:55.450 align:middle line:90%
it's made in the brain.

01:07:55.450 --> 01:07:59.550 align:middle line:84%
It's made in the pineal
gland of the brain

01:07:59.550 --> 01:08:01.950 align:middle line:84%
and it's got a very
powerful antioxidant

01:08:01.950 --> 01:08:03.830 align:middle line:90%
status compared with vitamins.

01:08:03.830 --> 01:08:10.290 align:middle line:84%
For example, melatonin is five
times as powerful as vitamin C

01:08:10.290 --> 01:08:17.050 align:middle line:84%
and twice as powerful as vitamin
E and it secretes only at night

01:08:17.050 --> 01:08:18.939 align:middle line:84%
and it's at night
that we need it

01:08:18.939 --> 01:08:20.740 align:middle line:84%
because that's
when we go to sleep

01:08:20.740 --> 01:08:23.891 align:middle line:84%
and when our brain repairs
the cells of our body.

01:08:23.891 --> 01:08:27.340 align:middle line:90%


01:08:27.340 --> 01:08:29.960 align:middle line:84%
And that's when melatonin
comes out to do its work.

01:08:29.960 --> 01:08:35.636 align:middle line:90%


01:08:35.636 --> 01:08:38.430 align:middle line:84%
NARRATOR: Each day our body
loses about half a billion

01:08:38.430 --> 01:08:43.415 align:middle line:84%
cells and at night, that's
when our body replaces

01:08:43.415 --> 01:08:48.149 align:middle line:84%
those cells through
a process called cell

01:08:48.149 --> 01:08:50.082 align:middle line:90%
mitosis, the dividing of cells.

01:08:50.082 --> 01:08:54.240 align:middle line:90%


01:08:54.240 --> 01:08:58.200 align:middle line:84%
What it's doing
is, it's mopping up

01:08:58.200 --> 01:09:00.319 align:middle line:90%
what are called free radicals.

01:09:00.319 --> 01:09:04.819 align:middle line:84%
These free radicals are really
the spare electrons left over

01:09:04.819 --> 01:09:08.800 align:middle line:84%
from the process of making the
energy which we need to repair

01:09:08.800 --> 01:09:11.588 align:middle line:90%
ourselves in the first place.

01:09:11.588 --> 01:09:13.810 align:middle line:84%
NARRATOR: Each night
as our body repairs

01:09:13.810 --> 01:09:17.050 align:middle line:84%
itself, millions of
free radical cells

01:09:17.050 --> 01:09:20.615 align:middle line:84%
are created as a
byproduct of cell mitosis.

01:09:20.615 --> 01:09:23.880 align:middle line:90%


01:09:23.880 --> 01:09:26.439 align:middle line:84%
These free radical cells
attack healthy cells.

01:09:26.439 --> 01:09:33.260 align:middle line:90%


01:09:33.260 --> 01:09:36.290 align:middle line:84%
It is universally agreed
that the free radical cell

01:09:36.290 --> 01:09:40.250 align:middle line:84%
is the main causal
factor in most cancer.

01:09:40.250 --> 01:09:42.800 align:middle line:84%
Our body's main defense
against these free radicals

01:09:42.800 --> 01:09:46.046 align:middle line:84%
is its most powerful
antioxidant, melatonin.

01:09:46.046 --> 01:09:49.700 align:middle line:90%


01:09:49.700 --> 01:09:53.200 align:middle line:84%
It passes into the
blood stream and its job

01:09:53.200 --> 01:09:56.340 align:middle line:84%
is to act as a
natural antioxidant,

01:09:56.340 --> 01:09:58.710 align:middle line:90%
a natural anti cancer agent.

01:09:58.710 --> 01:10:03.200 align:middle line:84%
Melatonin is a very, very
powerful anti-cancer agent.

01:10:03.200 --> 01:10:06.600 align:middle line:84%
What it does is
it acts as what's

01:10:06.600 --> 01:10:08.850 align:middle line:84%
called an oncostatic
agent, that is

01:10:08.850 --> 01:10:11.220 align:middle line:90%
it protects you against cancer.

01:10:11.220 --> 01:10:14.810 align:middle line:84%
It controls the
sleep-wake cycle so

01:10:14.810 --> 01:10:16.270 align:middle line:84%
that you get a good
night's sleep when

01:10:16.270 --> 01:10:17.900 align:middle line:90%
you've got proper melatonin.

01:10:17.900 --> 01:10:20.510 align:middle line:90%
It's an anti-aging molecule.

01:10:20.510 --> 01:10:23.720 align:middle line:84%
In other words, by mopping
up those free radicals,

01:10:23.720 --> 01:10:27.385 align:middle line:84%
it leaves your skin and
complexion looking younger.

01:10:27.385 --> 01:10:34.170 align:middle line:90%


01:10:34.170 --> 01:10:38.750 align:middle line:84%
We have in our lab
12,000 studies,

01:10:38.750 --> 01:10:41.060 align:middle line:84%
which we've collected
over the years

01:10:41.060 --> 01:10:43.370 align:middle line:84%
and that is more
studies than have ever

01:10:43.370 --> 01:10:46.750 align:middle line:84%
been published on
paracetamol, which is the most

01:10:46.750 --> 01:10:49.980 align:middle line:90%
common headache reliever.

01:10:49.980 --> 01:10:53.220 align:middle line:84%
There is more scientific
interest in melatonin

01:10:53.220 --> 01:10:54.990 align:middle line:90%
than there is in paracetamol.

01:10:54.990 --> 01:10:59.044 align:middle line:90%


01:10:59.044 --> 01:11:00.900 align:middle line:84%
INTERVIEWER: What are the
consequences of having

01:11:00.900 --> 01:11:03.130 align:middle line:84%
a reduced amount of melatonin?
-Yeah.

01:11:03.130 --> 01:11:05.680 align:middle line:84%
Well, if you have a reduced
amount of melatonin, what

01:11:05.680 --> 01:11:09.300 align:middle line:84%
happens then is that your
immune system starts to be

01:11:09.300 --> 01:11:11.660 align:middle line:90%
less competent, for a start.

01:11:11.660 --> 01:11:13.600 align:middle line:84%
You tend to get
sleep disturbance.

01:11:13.600 --> 01:11:15.310 align:middle line:84%
You can get off to
sleep or if you do,

01:11:15.310 --> 01:11:19.510 align:middle line:84%
you wake up and can't
get back to sleep.

01:11:19.510 --> 01:11:24.250 align:middle line:84%
You can have heart
complications because melatonin

01:11:24.250 --> 01:11:25.750 align:middle line:90%
protects your heart as well.

01:11:25.750 --> 01:11:30.790 align:middle line:90%


01:11:30.790 --> 01:11:33.260 align:middle line:84%
And you're much more
prone to disease

01:11:33.260 --> 01:11:37.450 align:middle line:84%
because your immune system is
not functioning at its best.

01:11:37.450 --> 01:11:39.470 align:middle line:84%
So these are some of the
things that happen when you

01:11:39.470 --> 01:11:41.250 align:middle line:90%
have a lowered melatonin level.

01:11:41.250 --> 01:11:45.580 align:middle line:84%
And for example, the average
woman with breast cancer

01:11:45.580 --> 01:11:48.480 align:middle line:84%
has only got 1/10
of the melatonin

01:11:48.480 --> 01:11:51.000 align:middle line:90%
of a normal woman of her age.

01:11:51.000 --> 01:11:54.770 align:middle line:90%


01:11:54.770 --> 01:11:57.220 align:middle line:84%
And for people with
prostate cancer,

01:11:57.220 --> 01:12:00.060 align:middle line:84%
they've got less than
half the melatonin

01:12:00.060 --> 01:12:03.070 align:middle line:90%
that they should have.

01:12:03.070 --> 01:12:06.300 align:middle line:84%
Autistic children have less
than half melatonin levels

01:12:06.300 --> 01:12:09.260 align:middle line:90%
that they should enjoy.

01:12:09.260 --> 01:12:13.490 align:middle line:84%
Reduced melatonin in
night shift workers--

01:12:13.490 --> 01:12:15.390 align:middle line:84%
because they're working at
night and exposed to light;

01:12:15.390 --> 01:12:18.040 align:middle line:84%
they don't produce
nocturnal melatonin--

01:12:18.040 --> 01:12:22.570 align:middle line:84%
is known to produce a 50%
increase in breast cancer risk.

01:12:22.570 --> 01:12:26.190 align:middle line:84%
And the International Agency
for Research on Cancer, IARC,

01:12:26.190 --> 01:12:30.540 align:middle line:84%
has actually classed night
shift work as a class

01:12:30.540 --> 01:12:36.750 align:middle line:84%
to a probable carcinogen because
of its melatonin reduction.

01:12:36.750 --> 01:12:39.630 align:middle line:84%
There are lots of studies now
showing that people on night

01:12:39.630 --> 01:12:44.040 align:middle line:84%
shifts or people who are blind
have different cancer rates

01:12:44.040 --> 01:12:48.060 align:middle line:84%
than the average population
and most of those studies

01:12:48.060 --> 01:12:50.650 align:middle line:84%
support the view
that the absence

01:12:50.650 --> 01:12:56.696 align:middle line:84%
or the lowered melatonin has
an adverse effect on health.

01:12:56.696 --> 01:13:00.390 align:middle line:84%
NARRATOR: Because the body
only repairs itself at night,

01:13:00.390 --> 01:13:03.450 align:middle line:84%
melatonin is only produced
when the pineal gland senses

01:13:03.450 --> 01:13:04.621 align:middle line:90%
that no light is present.

01:13:04.621 --> 01:13:08.060 align:middle line:90%


01:13:08.060 --> 01:13:12.040 align:middle line:84%
What happens is that the
pineal gland is light sensitive.

01:13:12.040 --> 01:13:14.990 align:middle line:10%
It's sitting right
where your brain

01:13:14.990 --> 01:13:17.420 align:middle line:10%
receives signals from
your eyes, that crossover

01:13:17.420 --> 01:13:18.750 align:middle line:10%
point in the middle.

01:13:18.750 --> 01:13:22.820 align:middle line:84%
It's called the suprachiasmatic
nuclei and that the connections

01:13:22.820 --> 01:13:25.790 align:middle line:84%
from there goes directly
to the pineal gland

01:13:25.790 --> 01:13:28.740 align:middle line:84%
to tell it whether there's
any light around or not.

01:13:28.740 --> 01:13:30.720 align:middle line:84%
If there is light
around, then there's

01:13:30.720 --> 01:13:33.530 align:middle line:84%
also interference
with the signals

01:13:33.530 --> 01:13:38.530 align:middle line:84%
the brain wants to send to our
cells in order to repair them.

01:13:38.530 --> 01:13:41.130 align:middle line:84%
So it says there is no point in
the brain sending these signals

01:13:41.130 --> 01:13:43.760 align:middle line:84%
out to our cells to
tell them to repair

01:13:43.760 --> 01:13:45.310 align:middle line:84%
because there's so
much interference

01:13:45.310 --> 01:13:46.500 align:middle line:90%
that they won't hear it.

01:13:46.500 --> 01:13:49.615 align:middle line:84%
So the brain waits
until it's dark.

01:13:49.615 --> 01:14:04.465 align:middle line:90%


01:14:04.465 --> 01:14:06.100 align:middle line:84%
INTERVIEWER: What
kind of research

01:14:06.100 --> 01:14:08.556 align:middle line:84%
is shown that there is
an effect on melatonin

01:14:08.556 --> 01:14:13.620 align:middle line:84%
production from electric fields,
magnetic fields, radio waves?

01:14:13.620 --> 01:14:14.320 align:middle line:90%
Right.

01:14:14.320 --> 01:14:19.000 align:middle line:84%
Well, the Battelle
Institute in America

01:14:19.000 --> 01:14:23.520 align:middle line:84%
has done a lot of work on this
way back from the late 1970s,

01:14:23.520 --> 01:14:24.980 align:middle line:90%
in fact.

01:14:24.980 --> 01:14:29.260 align:middle line:84%
And their scientists there,
Barry Wilson and Dick Stevens

01:14:29.260 --> 01:14:32.120 align:middle line:84%
and people like that,
started thinking

01:14:32.120 --> 01:14:37.510 align:middle line:84%
that because we know that
if you turn the light on,

01:14:37.510 --> 01:14:40.660 align:middle line:84%
then the brain stops making
melatonin, they thought,

01:14:40.660 --> 01:14:43.280 align:middle line:84%
well, maybe our brains
can't distinguish

01:14:43.280 --> 01:14:47.960 align:middle line:84%
between electric fields that
we make ourselves artificially

01:14:47.960 --> 01:14:51.410 align:middle line:84%
and the natural light
that we all know this

01:14:51.410 --> 01:14:53.960 align:middle line:84%
happens during the daytime
because we just don't

01:14:53.960 --> 01:14:56.500 align:middle line:90%
make melatonin in the daytime.

01:14:56.500 --> 01:14:58.380 align:middle line:90%
Very good biological reasons.

